## Summary

This study developed a head-mounted device for quantifying bidirectional face-to-face behavior among multiple people. The work focused on measuring interpersonal face-to-face interaction using wearable sensing technology.

The study contributes to the Measuring and HCI lines by providing a device-based method for recording face-to-face behavior in multi-person interaction. It also provides a basis for later wearable systems such as FaceLooks.

## Research line

- **Measuring**: quantification of bidirectional face-to-face behavior
- **HCI**: wearable device design for human–human interaction measurement
- **Human–Human Interaction**: recording face-to-face behavior among multiple people

